{{unreferenced|date=November 2012}} In [[telecommunication]], an '''isochronous signal''' is a [[Signalling (telecommunication)|signal]] in which the [[time]] interval separating any two significant instants is equal to the [[Unit interval (data transmission)|unit interval]] or a multiple of the unit interval. Variations in the time intervals are constrained within specified limits.
"[[Isochronous]]" is a characteristic of one signal, while "[[Synchronization|synchronous]]" indicates a relationship between two or more signals.
